CatDescriptText: Portion of article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Nixon Directs Republicans to Stress Highest Wages and Defense of Formosa - vice President Richard M. Nixon spent four action-packed hours in Pittsburgh last Friday, arriving at 11 A.M. and leaving at 3 P.M.  He addressed a crowd of over 3,000 at Syria Mosque..."
TitMainTitle: Vice President Richard Milhous Nixon and two men, possibly Arthur T. McGonigle on left, and Hugh Scott on right, standing at podium in Syria Mosque for 1958 Republican campaign
